column2:
adj
  1. striving to equal or excel, rivaling
  2. in a bad sense, envious, jealous

verb
  1. I hew, chop into shape, fashion, devise

verb
  1. to warm, to make warm, to keep warm

pron
  1. (in the singular) he, she, it
  2. (in the plural) they

verb
  1. I strike, beat, pound, knock
  2. I stamp, coin (money)

verb
  1. cause to emit light, cause to shine, ignite

verb
  1. to hang, put in a hanging position

verb
  1. to reckon, to calculate
  2. to think, to deem, to judge

verb
  1. to taste
  2. to discern, can tell apart, know (the difference?)

verb
  1. to cut, to tear, to rend, to separate

det
  1. his, her, its, their (own); third-person reflexive possessive

verb
  1. to be amazed or confounded, be struck senseless

noun
  1. stretch; or section, period (of time. See etymology)
  2. time

verb
  1. I vow, promise; dedicate or devote to a deity.
  2. I wish for, desire.
